year. During Sun’s transit from Cp to Ge, we have Uttara (north) ayana.		  During Sun’s transit from Cn to Sg, we have Dakshina (south) ayana.		  6 Ritu roughly means a “season”. There are 6 ritus in a year. They are – vasanta (spring), greeshma         (summer), varsha (rain), hemanta (dew), seeta (winter), sisira (fall). Each ritu consists of 2 months.</li>	</ul>  </div>  <!-- Planets and Time Periods ::: End -->  <!-- Planets and Tastes ::: Start -->  <div><h4><b>5. Planets and Tastes</b></h4></div>  <div class="table-responsive">   <table class="table">    <thead>      <tr>        <th>S.No.</th>        <th>Planets</th>        <th>Tastes</th>      </tr>    </thead>	<tbody>      <tr><td>1</td><td>Sun</td><td>Pungent taste (e.g. onion, ginger, pepper)</td></tr>	  <tr><td>2</td><td>Moon</td><td>Saline taste (e.g. sea salt, rock salt)</td></tr>	  <tr><td>3</td><td>Mars</td><td>Bitter taste (e.g. karela/bitter melon, dandelion root, rhubarb root, neem leaves)</td></tr>	  <tr><td>4</td><td>Mercury</td><td>Mixed taste</td></tr>	  <tr><td>5</td><td>Jupiter</td><td>Sweetness (e.g. sugar, dates)</td></tr>	  <tr><td>6</td><td>Venus</td><td>Sour taste (e.g. lemon, tamarind)</td></tr>	  <tr><td>7</td><td>Saturn</td><td>Astringent taste (e.g. plantain, pomegranate)</td></tr>    </tbody>   </table>  </div><!--/.table-responsive -->  <div>   <ul>     <li>2nd house shows one’s preference in food and the planets influencing it may decide one’s favorite taste.</li>	 <li>In addition, one should avoid the tastes of the planets who are likely bring disease. Suppose one is running a 	 dasa or antardasa of a sign containing Moon as per Shoola dasa (a dasa that shows suffering). Then some suffering 	 related to Moon is possible. Moon can give problems related to blood pressure as he governs blood. So eating too much 	 salty food during such a period may result in high blood pressure. Similarly, one should cut down on sweets during a 	 period in which Jupiter related troubles are indicated. Or, one may develop too much fat (Jupiter) or get	 other Jupiter related diseases.</li>   </ul>  </div>  <!-- Planets and Tastes ::: End --> </div><!--/.col-xs-6 --> <div class="col-xs-6">  <!-- Planetary Cabinet and its Main Governance ::: Start -->  <div><h4><b>6. Planetary Cabinet and its Main Governance</b></h4></div>  <div class="table-responsive">	<table class="table">	  <thead>      <tr>        <th>Planets</th>		<th>Planetary Cabinet</th>        <th>Person's Governance</th>      </tr>     </thead>     <tbody>      <tr><td>Sun</td><td>King</td><td>Soul</td></tr>	  <tr><td>Moon</td><td>King</td><td>Mind</td></tr>	  <tr><td>Mars</td><td>Leader (Army chief)</td><td>Strength</td></tr>	  <tr><td>Mercury</td><td>Prince</td><td>Speech</td></tr>	  <tr><td>Jupiter</td><td>Minister</td><td>Knowledge and happiness</td></tr>	  <tr><td>Venus</td><td>Minister</td><td>Potency</td></tr>	  <tr><td>Saturn</td><td>Servant</td><td>Grief</td></tr>	  <tr><td>Rahu</td><td>Army</td><td>-</td></tr>	  <tr><td>Ketu</td><td>Army</td><td>-</td></tr>     </tbody>	</table><!--/.table -->   </div><!--/.table-responsive -->  <!-- Planetary Cabinet and its Main Governance ::: End -->  <!-- Planets and Gunas ::: Start -->  <div><h4><b>7. Planets: Gunas</b></h4></div>  <div class="table-responsive">   <table class="table">    <thead>      <tr>        <th>Saattwik</th>        <th>Raajasik</th>        <th>Taamasik</th>      </tr>    </thead>    <tbody>      <tr><td>Sun</td><td>Mercury</td><td>Mars</td></tr>	  <tr><td>Moon</td><td>Venus</td><td>Saturn</td></tr>	  <tr><td>Jupiter</td><td></td><td></td></tr>    </tbody>   </table>  </div><!--/.table-responsive -->  <!-- Planets and Gunas ::: Start -->  <!-- Planetary Abodes ::: Start -->  <div><h4><b>8. Planets: Planetary Abodes</b></h4></div>  <div><b>Planetary Abodes:</b> Planet's place of Residence</div>  <div class="table-responsive">   <table class="table">    <thead>      <tr>        <th>S.No.</th>        <th>Planets</th>        <th>Planetary Abodes</th>      </tr>    </thead>	<tbody>      <tr><td>1</td><td>Sun</td><td>Temple</td></tr>	  <tr><td>2</td><td>Moon</td><td>Watery place</td></tr>	  <tr><td>3</td><td>Mercury</td><td>Sports Ground</td></tr>	  <tr><td>4</td><td>Jupiter</td><td>Treasure house</td></tr>	  <tr><td>5</td><td>Venus</td><td>Bedroom</td></tr>	  <tr><td>6</td><td>Saturn</td><td>Filthy area</td></tr>    </tbody>   </table>  </div><!--/.table-responsive -->  <!-- Planetary Abodes ::: End -->  <!-- Sapta Dhaatus ::: Start -->  <div><h4><b>9. Planets: Sapta Dhaatus</b></h4></div>  <div><b>Sapta Dhaatus:</b> 7 matters make up human body</div>  <div class="table-responsive">   <table class="table">    <thead>      <tr>        <th>S.No.</th>        <th>Planets</th>        <th>Sapta Dhaatus</th>      </tr>    </thead>	<tbody>      <tr><td>1</td><td>Sun</td><td>Bones</td></tr>	  <tr><td>2</td><td>Moon</td><td>Blood</td></tr>	  <tr><td>3</td><td>Mars</td><td>Marrow</td></tr>	  <tr><td>4</td><td>Mercury</td><td>Skin</td></tr>	  <tr><td>5</td><td>Jupiter</td><td>Fat</td></tr>	  <tr><td>6</td><td>Venus</td><td>Semen (materials related to the reproductive system)</td></tr>	  <tr><td>7</td><td>Saturn</td><td>Muscles</td></tr>    </tbody>   </table>  </div><!--/.table-responsive -->  <div>    <ul>	 <li>If Sun is afflicted, it can show some problems related to bones. Weakness of Moon		 may give blood related problems. And so on</li>	</ul>  </div>  <!-- Sapta Dhaatus ::: End -->  <!-- Planets and Ritus ::: Start -->  <div><h4><b>10. Planets and Ritus</b></h4></div>  <div class="table-responsive">   <table class="table">    <thead>      <tr>        <th>S.No.</th>        <th>Planets</th>        <th>Ritus (Seasons)</th>      </tr>    </thead>	<tbody>      <tr><td>1</td><td>Sun</td><td></td></tr>	  <tr><td>2</td><td>Moon</td><td>Varsha Ritu (Rainy)</td></tr